{
  "stem": "25651.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Michael Honey.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Michael, M-I-C-H-A-E-L.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Honey, H-O-N-E-Y.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Formerly Honigwachs, H-O-N-I-G-W-A-C-H-S.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had a nickname as a very small child, before I went to school, which my brother, [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Milos, ?] gave me, and that was Puppe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Puppe means dolly.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was apparently quite a beautiful child, hence the name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The funny thing is that because I was a boy, or I am a boy, [LAUGHS] in German, they called me derr Puppe, derr being the personal pronoun, masculine.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in fact, the correct German says die Puppe, not derr Puppe.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So whenever I was introduced, in German, to people and people said, this is derr Puppe, everybody started laughing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When I went to my first class at elementary school, at age six, and we were asked what our nicknames were and I said my nickname was Puppe, the teacher, who was a very lovely man, said, oh, you can't go through life with a name like that.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he said, to me, well, you look like a little bear, so I will call you Misha, which is the Czech sort of diminutive of a bear.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My date of birth is the 3rd of September, 1929.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm 67.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in Novy Jicin, N-O-V-Y, separate word Jicin, J-I-C with a hook I-- long I-- N.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Which is in Moravia in Czechoslovakia, or what used to be Czechoslovakia, now the Czech Republic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it's, in fact, in the part of Czechoslovakia which, in prewar days, was called the Sudetenland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name is Salomon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's name is Adele Cirla.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's on her birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Her Hebrew name is [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Tsila, ?] and in her letters to us at various times that she wrote, she always signed herself [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Tsila. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
